Message(content='```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "# solution.py\\n\\nclass OfficeTaskScheduler:\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n    The OfficeTaskScheduler class is designed to manage and schedule tasks for multiple team members within an office environment.\\n    It allows users to create, assign, track tasks, set deadlines and priorities, and monitor progress.\\n    \\"\\"\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Initialize the OfficeTaskScheduler with empty data structures for tasks.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        self.tasks = {}  # Dictionary to store tasks with their details\\n\\n    def create_task(self, task_id, description, assignee, deadline, priority):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Create a new task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :param description: Description of the task\\n        :param assignee: Person assigned to the task\\n        :param deadline: Deadline for the task\\n        :param priority: Priority level of the task\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\"Task with ID {task_id} already exists.\\")\\n        self.tasks[task_id] = {\\n            \'description\': description,\\n            \'assignee\': assignee,\\n            \'deadline\': deadline,\\n            \'priority\': priority,\\n            \'status\': \'Pending\'\\n        }\\n\\n    def assign_task(self, task_id, assignee):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Assign a task to a different person.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :param assignee: New person assigned to the task\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\"Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\\")\\n        self.tasks[task_id][\'assignee\'] = assignee\\n\\n    def update_task_status(self, task_id, status):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Update the status of a task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :param status: New status of the task (e.g., \'Pending\', \'In Progress\', \'Completed\')\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\"Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\\")\\n        self.tasks[task_id][\'status\'] = status\\n\\n    def get_task_details(self, task_id):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Get details of a specific task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        :return: Dictionary containing task details\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\"Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\\")\\n        return self.tasks[task_id]\\n\\n    def list_tasks(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        List all tasks.\\n        :return: List of dictionaries containing task details\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        return list(self.tasks.values())\\n\\n    def remove_task(self, task_id):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Remove a task.\\n        :param task_id: Unique identifier for the task\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        if task_id not in self.tasks:\\n            raise ValueError(f\\"Task with ID {task_id} does not exist.\\")\\n        del self.tasks[task_id]"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` file includes a basic implementation of the `OfficeTaskScheduler` class with methods to create, assign, update, retrieve, list, and remove tasks. Each task is stored in a dictionary with details such as description, assignee, deadline, priority, and status.', role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)
